properties.areaDesc: Coastal Cameron; Inland Cameron; Inland Willacy; Coastal Willacy
properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued January 9 at 4:16PM CST until January 10 at 8:00PM CST by NWS Brownsville TX
properties.description:
* WHAT...South winds 30 to 40 mph with gusts up to 50 mph
expected.

* WHERE...Inland Willacy, Inland Cameron, Coastal Willacy and
Coastal Cameron Counties.

* WHEN...From 9 AM to 8 PM CST Friday.

* IMPACTS...Gusty winds will blow around unsecured objects. Tree
limbs will be blown down and a few power outages will result.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Minor structural damage, such as metal
siding, will be likely due to these high winds. Unsecured
lightweight items, including remaining holiday decorations,
will blow away.
properties.instruction:
High profile or light weight vehicles will be difficult to
drive...especially on bridges or overpasses and in cross winds.
Secure loose items.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 9 AM TO 8 PM CST FRIDAY
